Rwanda Says its Gets a $30 Million World Bank Grant for Skills Development

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-05-04T08:15:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/rwanda-says-its-gets-a-30-million-world-bank-grant-for-skills-development.html
Rwanda received $36.5 million of
grants to develop skills and a strategic plan for the
environment, the Finance and Economic Planning Ministry said.  The East African will receive $30 million from the  World
Bank  for skills development and $6.5 million from  Sweden  to
implement its climate-change plan, the Kigali-based ministry
said on its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  